                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15184063" author="rsivaram" created="Tue, 8 Mar 2016 00:08:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since Mode is used by both SSL and SASL, perhaps SslMode is a bit confusing?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15184069" author="ijuma" created="Tue, 8 Mar 2016 00:12:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s true, it&apos;s also used to decide whether to create a `SaslClientAuthenticator` or `SaslServerAuthenticator` (and SSL mode for SASL_SSL). `ConnectionMode` may be better, not sure. Whatever we do, we should at least document it. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15184136" author="gwenshap" created="Tue, 8 Mar 2016 01:11:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe we can change Mode to loginType and loginType to jaasConfigurationSection?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15184139" author="gwenshap" created="Tue, 8 Mar 2016 01:12:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;actually, I like connectionMode better. But I still think that loginType says nothing about loginType and should have a better name.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17082977" author="chia7712" created="Tue, 14 Apr 2020 08:11:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this still available? ConnectionMode is a good name to me&#160;as this&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/ca0c071c108c9fd31a759e1cd1c4f89bdc5ac47e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;commit&lt;/a&gt; had mentioned &quot;Connection mode&quot; (see below)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connection mode for SSL and SASL connections.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
